OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1777903631
OL,3,CKemi Badenoch apologises for Bloody
OL,4,CSunday footage in social media video
OL,6,FThe Conservative Party apologised on
OL,7,FFriday for using the clips in its
OL,8,Fsocial media video, and said that as
OL,9,Fsoon as it was brought to its
OL,10,Fattention, it was removed.
OL,12,FAsked about the clip during a visit in
OL,13,Fsouth-east London, Mrs Badenoch said:
OL,14,F"I have apologised. I did not sign off
OL,15,Fthe video.
OL,26,@vD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/6
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1777903631
OL,3,CKemi Badenoch apologises for Bloody
OL,4,CSunday footage in social media video
OL,6,F"It was about a vote in parliament
OL,7,Fwhere Labour are putting in
OL,8,Flegislation that is hounding the very
OL,9,Felderly veterans for things that
OL,10,Fhappened decades ago, often under the
OL,11,Finstruction of political leaders who
OL,12,Fare no longer around.
OL,14,F"We support our veterans, but the
OL,15,Fvideo was done by very young people
OL,16,Fwho did not recognise the footage as
OL,17,Fbeing from Bloody Sunday.
OL,19,F"So I apologise as well that that
OL,20,Fvideo went out in error.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU{D@AOU
